as owners, tenants, usufructuary or other beneficial owners, as well as lessors who lease a business as a whole but have not given up if the requirements of Section 140 AO are met or one of the accounting limits set out in Section 141 Paragraph 1 AO is exceeded"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "When making the assessment, care must be taken to ensure that businesses that are required to keep accounts in accordance with Section 141 (1) AO are informed in good time of the start of the accounting obligation"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "If the accounting obligation is no longer required, Section 141 (2) AO does not provide for a formal notification, but in these cases a corresponding note in the tax assessment or a special notification is considered appropriate for reasons of legal certainty"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "For the rest, reference is made to the following instructions regarding the accounting obligation in agricultural and forestry operations: Rdvfg"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "from 18 12 1980 - S-2230 / S-0311 A - St 34 2 / St 42 1 - Tz"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "1 -; FM decree of 27 3 1981 - S-2230 A - 442 - No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "5 (corresponds to BMF letter of 27 3 1981 BStBl I S"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "282; ESt-Kartei: Card 7 to \u00a7 13 EStG); FM-Decree of 15 12 1981 - S-2163 A - 442 - No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "1 and 2 (corresponds to BMF letter of 15 12 1981 BStBl I S"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "878; ESt-Kartei: Map 15 to \u00a7 13 EStG); Section 127 EStR 199012 Livestock assessment For the assessment of livestock - with the exception of horses - those with Rdvfg"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "vom 26 5 1967 - S-2132a A - St 32 2 - (BStBl II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "239) established average values"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "For horses acquired by the taxpayer or born in the taxpayer's business after the beginning of the 1980/81 financial year, the horses listed in the Rdvfg"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "vom 24 3 1981 - S-2132a A - St 34 2 - ESt-Kartei: Map 6 to \u00a7 13 EStG - contained values \u200b\u200bare decisive"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "Incidentally, also Section 125 EStR 199013 Flat-rate amounts for personal consumption and meals Generally applicable flat-rate amounts that can be used on a large scale in practice can no longer be determined with regard to the specialization of the companies in certain branches of production"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "14 Assessment of plant stocks in tree nurseries For the assessment of plant stocks in tree nurseries, the FM decree of 9 1 1991 - S-2163 A - 442 - (corresponds to BMF letter of 9 1 1991 BStBl I S"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "133; ESt-Kartei: card 2 to \u00a7 13 EStG) approved simplification regulations essential"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "15 Value in use of the apartment The income from agriculture and forestry includes until the last application of Section 13 (2) No. 2 EStG (reference to Section 52 (15) EStG and FM decree of 12 11 1986 - S-2236 A - 442 - corresponds BMF letter dated 12 11 1986 BStBl IS"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "528; Income tax card: card 3 to \u00a7 52 EStG) also the (gross) value in use of the taxpayer's apartment if the apartment does not exceed the size customary for businesses of the same type"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "The profit of the financial year in which the value-in-use taxation ceases to apply, including the value in use still to be assessed for part of the financial year, is to be divided proportionally in accordance with Section 4a (2) No. 1 of the Income Tax Act"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "If the value-in-use taxation is retrospectively deselected, the application also regularly affects the amount of the previous year's income"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "If the assessment of the previous year has already been finalized, it must be changed in accordance with Section 175 (1) No. 2 AO"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "The rental value is to be regularly estimated in analogous application of Section 8 (2) EStG, whereby the local average rent for apartments of a comparable type, location and equipment (market rent) is decisive"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "If the rental value is determined according to the rent index drawn up by the tax office,"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "still to take into account the rural conditions accordingly, as far as these have not yet been given special consideration in the rent index"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "In addition, agricultural holdings in the narrower sense (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "regularly not for special uses) by the BFH jurisprudence (judgments of 30 1 1974 BStBl II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "608 of 30 1 1974 BStBl 1975 II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "3 and from 28 3 1974 BStBl 1975 II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "9) to undertake approved deductions from the rental value, provided these have not yet been reflected in the rent index"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "Deductions are regularly considered because of the general value-reducing factors resulting from membership in agriculture (20 percent"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": ") and because of the special circumstances impairing the value of the individual case (up to 30 percent"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "The general discount of 20%"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "of the rental value customary in the location is not to be made in the case of businesses with special uses, viticulture or horticulture businesses in a normal location (cf. section II No. 17 of the minutes of the income tax group meeting 1987 of 8 9 1987 - S-2319 A - St 31 1 -)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "In addition, reference is made to Section 130 a Paragraph 7 EStR 1990"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "2 Determination of profits by comparing the operating income with the operating expenses21 General Because of the scope of the determination of profits according to \u00a7 4 Paragraph 3 EStG, I refer to Section 127 Paragraph 3 Income Tax Act 1990 (cf."}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "Section 17 Income Tax Act 1990)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "22 Average livestock values \u200b\u200bThe average valuation permitted for book-keeping farmers and foresters (cf."}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "12) can, according to Section 125 a of the Income Tax Act 1990, under certain conditions, be used in the determination of profits in accordance with Section 4 Paragraph 3 of the Income Tax Act"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "23 Value in use of the apartment In the cases of Section 4 (3) EStG, the value in use of the apartment is to be determined in accordance with the principles applicable to accounting operations (see"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "24 Maintaining the special register in accordance with Section 7a (8) of the EStGB When determining profits in accordance with Section 4 (3) of the EStG, special depreciation in accordance with Section 76 of the EStDV is permitted for the first time for the depreciable assets acquired or manufactured after June 26, 1982 up to the end of the 1991/92 financial year; their use requires records in accordance with Section 7a (8) of the Income Tax Act"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "These records in the special directory named in Section 7a (8) of the Income Tax Act must be made at the latest by the submission of the tax return for the financial year in which the beneficial asset was acquired or manufactured"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "It is not sufficient if the directory is only available at the time of a later application after submitting the tax return, e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "a later tax audit"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "3 Appraisal farmers31 General For farmers and foresters who are obliged to keep accounts but do not keep proper books, the profit is to be estimated in individual cases according to \u00a7 162 AO"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "The same applies to those farmers and foresters who are not obliged to keep accounts nor meet the requirements of Section 13a Paragraph 1 No. 2 and 3 EStG if they do not have any books in the sense of"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "of \u00a7 4 Abs 1 EStG and also the operating income and expenses i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "of Section 4 Paragraph 3 EStG (Section 127 Paragraph 2 - 4 EStR 1990)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "The estimate has - with the exception of the in Section 127 Paragraph 4 S."}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "7 second half-sentence of the EStR 1990 - to be carried out in accordance with the principles of Section 4 (1) EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "When making the estimate, all circumstances must be taken into account that are important for the estimate in individual cases (Section 162 (1) sentence 2 AO)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "The aim of the estimate must be to determine the profit actually achieved"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "Of several possible estimation methods (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "Asset growth calculation, total monetary transaction calculation or estimate based on the results of similar accounting operations) is therefore the one that comes closest to the result that would have been shown in proper accounting"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "In doing so, preference should always be given to the method that best takes into account the particular operational conditions of the individual case"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "The uncertainties inherent in an estimate are, however, at the expense of the taxpayer, who himself gave cause for the estimate by neglecting his tax cooperation obligations"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "It is important to ensure that farmers who are required to keep accounts and whose profit is estimated are to be reported to the tax auditor if an audit appears suitable or promises success for other reasons"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "This applies in particular to all agricultural businesses that have fulfilled their accounting obligations for some time, then no longer keep books and allow themselves to be valued"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "If a tax audit is planned in these cases, the assessment must be carried out subject to the review (Section 164 AO)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "32 Maintaining the special register in accordance with Section 7a (8) of the Income Tax Act (EStG) Insofar as agricultural holdings that are required to keep accounts and do not keep books use special depreciation in accordance with Article 76 of the Income Tax Act (EStDV), the time at which the special register in accordance with Article 7a (8) of the Income Tax Act (EStG) no"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "24 to be observed"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "33 Estimation of the profit according to standard rates It is basically left to the discretion of the tax office which estimation method to use in the individual case"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "As a rule, however, the profit will have to be estimated based on the results of similar accounting operations"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "The basis for this is a modified guideline rate estimate"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "If, in individual cases, an estimate tailored to the particular operational conditions is not to be preferred or other empirical rates are not available, the profit can be estimated as follows: Initial estimate (No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "331) + lease income (No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "332) + surcharges for profits or profits not settled with the initial estimate amount"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "Additional profits (No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "333) + value in use of the apartment (No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "334) -wage expenses (No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "335) -Lease expenses, debt interest, permanent burdens (No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "336) +"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "Other surcharges and reductions (No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "337) = profit of the financial year The estimate of profit according to this procedure must not lead to an obviously incorrect taxation"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "Are there any doubts as to whether the type of operation, e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "In the case of processing operations or operations with sugar beet cultivation, an accurate profit estimate in this form is even possible, I ask you to call in the agricultural audit or the responsible official agricultural expert (ALS)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "331 Initial estimate When determining the initial estimate, a distinction is made - as before - according to the following areas: Area I: Rheinpfalz and Rheinhessen (both the Rhine level), Koblenz-Neuwied Basin, Maifeld and Grafschaft Area II: all other areas The initial estimate per hectare of agricultural land for the 1992/93 marketing year: estimated starting amounts per hectare / LN area forage cultivation area in percent"}, {"