ion sector"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "Areas for buildings, courtyards, house gardens, paths, ditches, field edges, forestry, tobacco-growing, horticultural, fruit-growing or viticultural areas, as well as areas used for mining, low-lying, unpaved land and similar areas are not taken into account"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "A quarter of hats and half of fruit-growing areas with regular agricultural underuse are to be considered"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "If vegetables are grown as catch crops or catch crops, the corresponding areas are not to be excluded from the calculation of the relevant agricultural area because there is double use"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "For the extent of the forage cultivation area, I refer to No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "3334332 Lease income Lease income also for the provision of reference quantities, ground rent and hunting leases, reduced by proportionate operating expenses, e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "Property taxes must be added to the initial estimate if they are included in income from agriculture and forestry"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "This is the case when the leased or"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "Hereditary assets belong to the lessor's agricultural and forestry business assets"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "333 Surcharges for profits or profits not settled with the initial estimate"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "All profits from sustainable or one-off operating income that are not included in the initial estimate are to be added to the initial estimate"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "Such surcharges come z"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "Consideration for profits from the extraction and sale of land, profits from viticulture, profits from fruit and vegetable cultivation, profits from closure and severance distilleries, profits from tobacco production, profits from other special branches, profits from ancillary businesses, profits from abnormal animal husbandry, additional profits from sales of breeding cattle , Profits from the rental of buildings and parts of buildings that belong to the business assets, profits from the sale of milk quotas and sugar beet quotas and from a milk quota leasing"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "I would also like to point out the following: 3331 Removal and sale of land"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "on this point"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "713332 Viticulture, fruit and vegetable growing as well as distilleries For the determination of the corresponding profits, I refer to the information given in No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "423 circulars mentioned"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "3333 Tobacco growing According to the determinations made, the harvest yields in the Palatinate growing area have developed as follows (1 dt = 100 kg): Wj"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "Cultivation area haErtrag German"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "Monetary value DM net harvest dt / ha avg"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "-Price DM / dt net income DM / ha net total cultivation1990 / 911 208 2406217 158 118 199 171 314 201 1991/1991 / 921 129 247 1819 206 165 219 77717010 repayment of premium withheld from harvest 1988 in fy"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "1991/924906951992 / 9310152612920488987257478420183Geudertheimer (cigar goods) 1990/917061388592985091967670131721991/926821499810479719219869915360"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "1991/92: 490695307741992 / 936301694611821358269169818773Burley (cut material) 1990/91439945572993792156772166451991/9238187937942815230790320836"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "1991/92: 00001992 / 9332680217575524245994423221Virgin1990 / 9164721560230113277687881991 / 9266927783631