number of animals and converting them into VE, the procedure is in accordance with Section 124 a EStR 1990"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "For the remaining after deduction of the normal inventory excess inventory is for the Wirtschaftsjahr1992 / be recognized as profit 93: BeiDM / VERindviehhaltung1250Stallmast of K\u00e4lbern690Stallmast of calves (payroll process) 195Mastschweineverkauf280L\u00e4uferverkauf500Ferkelverkauf650Legehennen eggs sale Gro\u00dfhandel0Legehennen eggs sale Einzelhandel1080Aufzucht of Junghennen830Junggefl\u00fcgelmast280Entenmast750Putenmast1950G\u00e4nsemast2550Darauf attributable wages are not taken into account and therefore can be up or set down"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "When determining the abnormal animal husbandry and calculating the corresponding surcharge to the initial estimate, please contact the responsible ALS"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "3335 Breeding cattle sales Regarding the determination of the additional profits from breeding cattle sales, No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "424 accordingly"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "3336 payments for the abandonment of milk production or"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "The income tax treatment of the milk delivery remuneration and the remuneration for the temporary use of delivery reference quantities was last amended by FM decree of 15 4 1991 - S-2132 A - 442 - (corresponds to BMF letter of 15 4 1991 BStBl I S"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "497; ESt-Kartei: card 18 e to \u00a7 13 EStG) and FM-decree of 21 8 1991 - S-2132 A - 442 - (Rdvfg"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "from 15 4 1992 - S-2230 A - St 34 2 - No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "45) regulated"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "Corresponding fees are to be determined in individual cases on the basis of the relevant documents and added to the initial estimate"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "334 Value in use of the apartment"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "15 to determine the principles contained"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "Because the estimated starting amounts do not include the expenses for the owner-occupied apartment, 65 per cent"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "of the value in use as business expenses"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "The debt interest payable on the apartment (No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "336) and the increased deductions (No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "3372) can also be applied"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "335 Wage expenses In the case of the initial estimate (No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "331) it is assumed that the company is managed exclusively with unpaid workers"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "Wage expenses are therefore to be deducted from the initial estimate insofar as they relate to the profit settled with the initial estimate"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "If profits are recorded as a surcharge through individual calculation, care must be taken to ensure that any proportionate wage expenditure is not recorded twice (cf. in particular no"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "3332 and 3333)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "For the distribution of wage expenses required in individual cases, see Rdvfg"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "from 15 4 1992 - S-2230 A - St 34 2 - No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "46336 Lease expenses, debt interest, permanent charges These expenses can be deducted insofar as they represent operating expenses and have not already been taken into account in a surcharge calculation"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "Deductible expenses also include ongoing lease payments for the provision of reference quantities and payments for the temporary use of delivery reference quantities (quota leasing) in accordance with Section 7a of the Nineteenth Ordinance on the Amendment of the Milk Guarantee Quantity Offsetting of 28 3 1991 BGBl I S"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "799 (for income tax treatment, see no"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "3336); however, not payments aimed at the purchase of reference quantities"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "If the lessee does not (or no longer) tax a value in use for a jointly leased apartment, the part of the total rent that is attributable to the apartment cannot be deducted as business expenses"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "337 Other surcharges and reductions 3371 Other surcharges The estimated starting amount for the profit from agricultural use does not include any income that is generated in the context of agriculture, but which is not regularly generated on farms (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "Expert fees, breeding premiums, profits from the sale of fixed assets, profits from participation in cooperatives, stud fee income, feed money income, wages and remuneration for other services)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "Insofar as such facts are determined in individual cases - especially in the context of company audits -"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "to make a profit surcharge"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "Any compensation or subsidies from public funding programs are not included in the initial estimate"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "3372 Increased reductions"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "increased deductions for residential buildings according to \u00a7 7b EStG and increased deductions according to \u00a7\u00a7 82a, 82g and 82i EStDV"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "As far as increased deductions are used, the profit must be increased again by the depreciation already taken into account in the initial estimate according to Section 7 (4) EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "3373 Special depreciation according to \u00a7 76 EStDV"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "Acquisition or production of the beneficiary assets by the end of the 1991/92 financial year) of the corresponding requirements"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "After the expiry of the tax credit period of three financial years, however (at the end of the tax assessment period 1994, the tax benefit expires - \u00a7 52 Paragraph 1 No. 2 Letter"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "k EStG) to increase the initial estimate by a surcharge, since according to Section 7a (9) EStG, the residual value is the assessment basis for further deductions for wear and tear and otherwise excessive depreciation amounts would otherwise be taken into account by applying the initial estimate"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "The surcharge for a financial year results from the total of the special depreciation granted divided by the remaining useful life of the respective asset"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "The increase in the initial estimate is to be carried out for the remaining period of use"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "When using the preferential treatment for immovable assets with a useful life of more than 30 years as well as for conversions and extensions to these assets, a correction is not necessary in view of Section 76 (4) sentence 3 EStDV for reasons of simplification"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "In order to ensure that the surcharges are also taken into account in future assessments, the control sheet placed under form number \"ESt 7\" must be kept and attached to the income tax files"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "34 Standard sales rates The standard sales rates applicable for the 1992/93 financial year are set out in paragraph"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "331 printed overview of the estimated starting amounts for the respective types of business"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "35 Tax reduction according to \u00a7 34e EStG \u00a7 34e EStG, as amended by the Tax Amendment Act 1992, provides that the tax reduction does not apply for the first time for the assessment period 1992 even if the profit of the financial year beginning in the assessment period (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "due to failure to submit the tax return or balance sheet, only incomplete proof of operating income) was estimated"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "There is no estimate of profit within the meaning of this provision if parts of the operating expenses are permissiblely taken into account on the basis of the guide amounts (see Rdvfg"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "from 10 9 1993 - S-2233 A - St 34 2 - No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "8th; ESt-Kartei: card 8 to \u00a7 13 EStG)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "This also applies to the permissible application of the flat rate operating expenses according to \u00a7 51 EStDV for certain forestry operations"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "The estimate of the profit (according to no"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "33) on the basis of initial estimates, includes all of the business's usual operating income and expenses; The benefit of Section 34e EStG is therefore ruled out in this determination of profits - as in the case of a full estimate"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "Contrary to Section 213 (5) EStR 1990, the lessor of an agricultural and forestry business is not entitled to the tax reduction under Section 34e EStG (BFH judgment of 15 4 1993 BFH / NV 1994 p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "87), because he does not have the option of determining profits according to \u00a7 13a EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "The income guidelines will be adjusted accordingly"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "36 form"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "33 is available to the tax offices using the \"ESt 6\" form"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "4 Determination of profits according to average rates (\u00a7 13a EStG) 41 General To determine the profit from agriculture and forestry according to the average rates of \u00a7 13a paragraph 3 to 8 EStG, I refer to the following regulations: Rdvfg"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "from 18 12 1980 - S-2230 / S-0311 A - St 34 2 / St 42 1 Item"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "2; FM decree of 27 3 1981 - S-2230 A - 442 - No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "2 (corresponds to BMF letter of 27 3 1981 BStBl p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "282; ESt-Kartei: Card 7 to \u00a7 13 EStG, No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "2); Sections 127 and 130 a of the 1990 Income Tax Regulations When making the assessment, particular attention must be paid to the fact that the taxpayers in question are informed in good time if the prerequisites for determining profits according to average rates cease to exist (Section 13a, Paragraph 1, Sentence 2 of the Income Tax Act)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "The use of z"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "the estimated starting amounts according to no"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "331 or the indicative amounts in viticulture (see no"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "422 and Appendix 1 of the Rdvfg"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "from 10 9 1993 - S-2233 A - St 34 2 -; ESt-Kartei: card 8 to \u00a7 13 EStG) in the first financial year after the transition is contrary to an effective application according to \u00a7 13a paragraph 2 sentence 1 EStG (BFH judgment of 18 3 1993 BStBl II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "549)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "This right to choose presupposes that either proper bookkeeping or actual records of operating income and operating expenses are based on the profit determination presented for at least the 1 financial year"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "This is not the case if z"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "Parts of the operating expenses are estimated or applied with reference rates"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "42 Determination of profit The scheme for determining profit according to \u00a7 13a Paragraph 3 to 8 EStG results from the form \"Annex ESt 2L / 3L (91) - Profit determination according to \u00a7 13a EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "\"The taxpayer can choose whether the profit to be assessed in accordance with Section 13a (8) of the Income Tax Act is determined according to the principles of Section 4 (1) or Section 4 (3) of the Income Tax Act (Section 130a (8) sentence 9 of the 1990 Income Tax Act)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "Any loss resulting from Section 13a (8) of the Income Tax Act (EStG) must be offset against the average rate profit in accordance with Section 13a (3) to (7) of the Income Tax Act"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "The exemption of max"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "3000 DM is only to be taken into account if the sum of the profits according to \u00a7 13a Abs 8 EStG is positive"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "The granting of the exemption cannot lead to a loss or change a loss"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "In the case of exclusive profits within the meaning of Section 13a Paragraph 8 EStG, even if the profit is actually determined in accordance with Section 4 Paragraph 3 or Section 4 Paragraph 1 EStG, the tax reduction in accordance with Section 34e EStG does not apply (BFH judgment of 28 November 1991 BStBl 1992 II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "458)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "421 Areas to be taken into account The 