{"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "To determine the physical work of the business owner as well as the unpaid relatives on the one hand and the paid workers on the other hand, if the initial value does not include the value of the special uses within the meaning of Section 13a Paragraph 4 No. 1 Sentence 2 EStG, I refer to the Rdvfg"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "from 15 4 1992 - S-2230 A - St 34 2 - No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "46; ESt-Kartei: Card 10 c to \u00a7 13 EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "423 Profits from special uses Pursuant to Section 13a (8) No. 1 EStG, profits from special uses must also be included in the average rate under the conditions specified there"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "For the determination of the profit from viticulture, I refer to the Rdvfg"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "vom 10 9 1993 - S-2233 A - St 34 2 - ESt-Kartei: Map 8 to \u00a7 13 EStG - and because of the determination of the profit from fruit and vegetable growing the Rdvfg"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "vom 15 12 1993 - S-2233 A - St 34 2 - ESt-Kartei: card 9 to \u00a7 13 EStG - to be observed"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "As far as profits from closure and severance distilleries are to be determined, I ask that the responsible agricultural Bp office be involved"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "This will inform the taxable district of the necessary reference rates and key figures"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "424 Profits from other business operations Profits from sales of breeding cattle that exceed a normal profit are to be recorded within the framework of Section 13a (8) No. 3 EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "A surcharge from the sale of breeding cattle is 70%"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "of the sales (auction) proceeds exceeding the initial value"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "The additional profit has to be calculated individually for each animal"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "A netting with sales proceeds that are below the initial values \u200b\u200bmay not be carried out"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "The decisive starting values \u200b\u200bfor the 1992/93 financial year are: for breeding horses 9000 DM for riding horses 7000 DM for breeding bulls 5300 DM for breeding cows 2300 DM for breeding cattle 2200 DM for breeding over 1,100 DM for breeding sows 1000 DM for breeding rams1300 DM"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "The following operating processes, which were not taken into account when determining the initial value, should be included in accordance with Section 13a (8) No. 3 EStG: Profits from the rental of rooms to holiday guests, insofar as income from agriculture and forestry is involved (reference to Sect 103 para 7 BewRL), interest income, insofar as the capital claim is attributable to the business assets, profits from participation that belong to the agricultural and forestry business assets, profits from the rental of buildings and parts of buildings belonging to the agricultural business assets, profits from the sale of sugar beet quotas, profits from the Sale of milk quotas, unless the FM decree of 15 4 1991 - S-2132 A - 442 - (corresponds to BMF letter of 15 4 1991 BStBl IS"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "497; ESt-Kartei: card 18 e to \u00a7 13 EStG) is to be used (see also no"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "75), compensation for economic difficulties, see FM decrees of 5 3 1992 9 2 1993 and 1 7 1993 - S-2149 A - 442 - (corresponds to BMF letter of 5 3 1992 9 2 1993 and 1 7 1993 BStBl 1992 I S"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "187 and BStBl 1993 I S"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "241; ESt-Kartei: card 13 b to \u00a7 13 EStG), profits from an inter-company use of machines, which are achieved in the context of agriculture and forestry, are to be partially recorded"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "In this respect, reference is made to the ESt card index: Card 2 to Section 13a EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "5 Forestry 51 Acquisition of forest land In Section 212 Paragraph 1 Sentences 7 u"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "8 EStR 1990, for reasons of simplification, it is permitted that capitalized acquisition or production costs for standing wood are reduced annually by 3%"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "can be reduced"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "When acquiring forest land and when acquiring businesses and sub-businesses, the purchase price must therefore be properly divided between the land and the stocking (standing wood)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "Whether this has happened in individual cases is checked by the forestry expert from the regional tax office"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "I therefore ask you to report to the regional finance directorate in the relevant cases before carrying out the assessment, enclosing the files"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "In the case of the sale of forest land as well as the sale of businesses and sub-businesses, appropriate taxation is only guaranteed if the proceeds from the sale relate to the land (loss clause according to Section 55 (6) of the Income Tax Act) and to the forest as well as"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "on other assets (buildings, inventory, paths, etc."}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": ") is divided"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "The distribution of the sales proceeds and, if applicable,"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "In such cases, the corresponding book value is determined by the forestry expert from the regional finance directorate"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "I therefore ask that in each individual case, immediately after a sale becomes known (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "by means of a notification of sale from the real estate acquisition tax office) and before carrying out the corresponding assessment, enclosing the tax files and the standard value files of the regional finance office"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "In the case of the sale of a business or a part of the business, this only applies if the proceeds from the sale exceed the applicable exemptions (\u00a7 14 in conjunction with"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "V with \u00a7 16 EStG)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "If the taxpayer applies for such an exemption due to the sale of a business or part of a business, this must be pointed out in the submission report to the regional tax office"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "In principle, this also applies if the proceeds from the sale (incl"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "of the standing wood) for the forest parcel does not exceed the book value of the land"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "In the case of such a sale of well-stocked land for which the starting amount of DM 2 / sqm (\u00a7 55 Paragraph 1 in conjunction with"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "Paragraph 2 no"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "2 EStG) applies, nevertheless there is usually a loss - which is not deductible according to Section 55 (6) EStG - from the sale of the land (the value of the land with forestry use in Rhineland-Palatinate only exceptionally exceeds DM 050 / sqm) and with regard to the standing wood a - taxable - profit"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "53 Profit from the use of wood by valued farmers"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "If the actual operating expenses cannot be determined in such cases, there are no concerns about the operating expenses being reduced to 45 per cent"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "estimate the income from the use of wood"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "This flat rate covers all operating expenses for the financial year in which the wood was used (incl"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "the reforestation costs)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "Applications for the application of the reduced tax rates according to \u00a7 34b for extraordinary income from forestry due to a tariff reduction according to \u00a7 34b of the Income Tax Act for extraordinary wood use and wood use as a result of force majeure (calamity use) must be forwarded immediately to the regional tax office"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "The various uses achieved in a financial year must be verified in terms of quantity according to Section 34b (4) No. 2 EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "After a review by the forestry expert, the tax offices receive a notification of the amount of tax-privileged wood use based on a preliminary calculation"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "a) This preliminary calculation of the tax-privileged income according to \u00a7 34b EStG by the forestry expert is based on unaudited information from the taxpayer and the like"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "via the corresponding operating income (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "Raw wood revenues) and expenditures (possibly"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "reduced by grants)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "If this differs from the above"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "Notification of the information provided by the taxpayer from the amounts declared to the tax office in the context of the relevant income tax return, the discrepancy must be clarified by asking the taxpayer"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "If it is found that the fundamentals (operating income and expenses) of the calculation periods of the preliminary calculation have changed, the forestry expert must be called in again, submitting the original and changed application documents"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "b) The calculation and reporting of the extraordinary wood uses in accordance with Section 34b (1) EStG by the forestry expert is subject to recognition by the tax office responsible for the determination"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "Extraordinary uses of wood are uses that occur outside of the stipulated usage rate if they have taken place for economic reasons (Section 34b (1) No. 1 EStG)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "On the question of economic reasons, see"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "Section 204 Income Tax"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "If the uses shown in the preliminary calculation of tax-privileged income of the forestry expert as extraordinary wood uses are not as extraordinary wood uses i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "of \u00a7 34b EStG, they are to be assigned to normal use (overuse - overuse)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "An application of the reduced tax rates of \u00a7 34b EStG is not possible for these uses"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "c) From the assessment period 1990 onwards, the reduced tax rates of \u00a7 34b EStG are no longer dependent on an application from the taxpayer"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "6 Non-objection limits for non-cash partial retirement benefits Non-cash partial retirement benefits are deductible at their actual value, which must be proven in detail"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "If an individual record is not provided, the value of non-cash partial retirement benefits is to be estimated in accordance with Section 1, Paragraph 1 of SachBez V in the version applicable for the respective assessment period (Section 87, Paragraph 4, p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "7 EStR)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "For the age-sharing spouse, only 80%"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "to take this value into account (Section 1 (4) SachBezV)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "The following lists the non-objection limits, which are determined in accordance with Section 1 (1) SachBezV in the version applicable for the respective assessment period: 19921993 (BStBl 92 I S"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "50) (BStBl 93 I S"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "26) MealsHeating and lightingMealsHeating and lightingDMDMDMDMEIndividual36948213823850Old sharing couple6649147868821529The non-objection limits are not applicable if, on the basis of the company's profit determination documents, it is obvious that the costs attributable to the retirement sharing are lower"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "7 Miscellaneous71 Determination of capital gains - taxation of land gains I would like to draw your attention once again to the correct and timely recording of sales and land gains"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "In particular, I ask that the control material available, such as"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "Notices of sale of the real estate transfer tax offices to be evaluated promptly"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "72 Control reports Except in the usual cases (control reports for the purposes of the Bp, inheritance tax, wage tax, unit valuation, etc.)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "), particularly in the case of lease / usage relationships, control notifications must be prepared using the \"ESt 34 d\" form"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "The cases in which the individual lease / use ratio comprises agricultural areas of more than 2 ha or in which areas with special uses i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "of Section 13a Paragraph 4 No. 4 EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "I ask that incoming control reports as well as unit value reports always be evaluated promptly because of possible effects on the way in which the taxpayer's profit is determined"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "When evaluating them, it can be useful to consult the standard value files"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "The same also applies to the assessment of farmers and foresters, particularly when determining profits in accordance with Section 13a of the Income Tax Act"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "73 Advance payments for winter oilseed rape Reference to the BMF letter of 23 12 1993 - IV B 2 - S-2132 - 24/93 - BStBl 1994 I S"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "1774 Income tax treatment of \"Compensation to certain producers because of their participation in the non-marketing and conversion program\" according to"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "the non-marketer compensation regulation - NEV - of 20 8 1993 (Federal Law Gazette 1993 I p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "1510) It was asked how the o"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "Compensation is to be treated in terms of income tax in particular with regard to the following points: a) Time of recognition (when determining profits according to Section 4 Paragraph 1 EStG), b) Application of Sections 24 No. 1 a, 34 Paragraph 1 and 2 EStG, c) Recording when determining profit \u00a7 13a EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "In agreement with the Federal Ministry of Finance and the highest tax authorities of the other countries, I comment on this as follows: To a): The claim for compensation is at the time of the application, at the earliest on August 5, 1992 (taxpayers who have the claim for compensation before the announcement of the offer of the EC have asserted) to activate"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "Although the damaging event occurred in earlier financial years, the claim for compensation will only be concretized with the offer by the EC and acceptance by the taxpayer (application) (cf. a"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "BFH judgment of April 26, 1989 BStBl 1991 II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "213)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "re b): For the compensation, the tariff reduction according to \u00a7 24 No. 1 a i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "Section 34 (1) and (2) EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "It is a compensation for lost income, which is accumulated in an assessment period"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "The tariff reduction does not include interest"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "to c): The compensation is settled with the basic amount according to \u00a7 13a Abs 4 EStG (see FM decree of 14 3 1985 - (S-2132 A - 442 -; ESt-Kartei: card 18 to \u00a7 13 EStG)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "This does not apply to financial years of the compensation period in which \u00a7 13a EStG does not apply"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "For the treatment of changes in area in the meantime, No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "1 letter"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "c FM decree of 15 4 1991 - S-2132 A - 442 - (corresponds to BMF letter of 15 4 1991 BStBl I S"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "49); ESt-Kartei: card 18 e to \u00a7 13 EStG) accordingly"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "For the interest, Section 13a (8) No. 3 EStG applies"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107746.xml"}, "text": "Basis: FM decree of 27 January 1994 - S-2230 A - 442 -Income tax / wage tax / church taxAccountingProcedural law / tax codeCommercial law Company lawRhineland-PalatinateAgriculture"}]